    "abstract": "Teaching Cø / N*: A Graduate Instructor's Manual presents a fourteen-session graduate curriculum for the Cø / N* network-dynamics theory of minimal phenomenal consciousness. It integrates the core model with work on system boundaries, report-independent availability, scientific indeterminacy, component ablation, phenomenal character, and structural legibility; locates the model among integrated-information, global-workspace, recurrent-processing, higher-order, predictive-processing, biological, and eliminativist approaches; and supplies lecture notes, collaborative exercises, controlled evidence releases, worksheets, assessment rubrics, and adversarial validation protocols. The manual treats the theory conditionally, distinguishes profile-level from bearer-level conclusions, and emphasizes tests capable of disconfirming or revising the model. Its synthetic classroom values are pedagogical rather than empirical estimates.",
